#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="an9.39"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an9.39:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 9 "
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 9 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an9.39:0.2"
msgid "4. Mahāvagga "
msgstr "4. The Great Chapter "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "an9.39:0.3"
msgid "39. Devāsurasaṅgāmasutta "
msgstr "39. The War Between the Gods and the Demons "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: sc1
#. VAR: samupabyūḷho → samupabbūḷho (bj, pts1)
msgctxt "an9.39:1.1"
msgid "“Bhūtapubbaṃ, bhikkhave, devāsurasaṅgāmo samupabyūḷho ahosi. "
msgstr "“Once upon a time, mendicants, a battle was fought between the gods and the demons. "

#. VAR: parājayiṃsu → parājiyiṃsu (bj, s1-3, pts1, mr)
msgctxt "an9.39:1.2"
msgid "Tasmiṃ kho pana, bhikkhave, saṅgāme asurā jiniṃsu, devā parājayiṃsu. "
msgstr "In that battle the demons won and the gods lost. "

#. VAR: devā → devā bhītā (pts1)
#. VAR: apayiṃsuyeva → apayaṃsveva (bj) | apassiṃsveva (s1-3) | apayiṃsveva (pts1)
#. VAR: uttarenābhimukhā → uttarena mukhā (bj) | uttarābhimukhā (s1-3)
#. VAR: abhiyiṃsu → abhiyaṃsu (bj) | abhibhayiṃsu (s1-3)
msgctxt "an9.39:1.3"
msgid "Parājitā ca, bhikkhave, devā apayiṃsuyeva uttarenābhimukhā, abhiyiṃsu asurā. "
msgstr "Defeated, the gods fled north with the demons in pursuit. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an9.39:1.4"
msgid "Atha kho, bhikkhave, devānaṃ etadahosi: "
msgstr "Then the gods thought, "

msgctxt "an9.39:1.5"
msgid "‘abhiyanteva kho asurā. "
msgstr "‘The demons are still in pursuit. "

msgctxt "an9.39:1.6"
msgid "Yannūna mayaṃ dutiyampi asurehi saṅgāmeyyāmā’ti. "
msgstr "Why don’t we engage them in battle a second time?’ "

msgctxt "an9.39:1.7"
msgid "Dutiyampi kho, bhikkhave, devā asurehi saṅgāmesuṃ. "
msgstr "And so a second battle was fought between the gods and the demons. "

msgctxt "an9.39:1.8"
msgid "Dutiyampi kho, bhikkhave, asurāva jiniṃsu, devā parājayiṃsu. "
msgstr "And for a second time the demons won and the gods lost. "

msgctxt "an9.39:1.9"
msgid "Parājitā ca, bhikkhave, devā apayiṃsuyeva uttarenābhimukhā, abhiyiṃsu asurā. "
msgstr "Defeated, the gods fled north with the demons in pursuit. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli4.433, sc2
msgctxt "an9.39:2.1"
msgid "Atha kho, bhikkhave, devānaṃ etadahosi: "
msgstr "Then the gods thought, "

msgctxt "an9.39:2.2"
msgid "‘abhiyanteva kho asurā. "
msgstr "‘The demons are still in pursuit. "

msgctxt "an9.39:2.3"
msgid "Yannūna mayaṃ tatiyampi asurehi saṅgāmeyyāmā’ti. "
msgstr "Why don’t we engage them in battle a third time?’ "

msgctxt "an9.39:2.4"
msgid "Tatiyampi kho, bhikkhave, devā asurehi saṅgāmesuṃ. "
msgstr "And so a third battle was fought between the gods and the demons. "

msgctxt "an9.39:2.5"
msgid "Tatiyampi kho, bhikkhave, asurāva jiniṃsu, devā parājayiṃsu. "
msgstr "And for a third time the demons won and the gods lost. "

msgctxt "an9.39:2.6"
msgid "Parājitā ca, bhikkhave, devā bhītā devapuraṃyeva pavisiṃsu. "
msgstr "Defeated and terrified, the gods fled right into the castle of the gods. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. VAR: pana → puna (mr)
msgctxt "an9.39:2.7"
msgid "Devapuragatānañca pana, bhikkhave, devānaṃ etadahosi: "
msgstr "When they had entered their castle, they thought, "

msgctxt "an9.39:2.8"
msgid "‘bhīruttānagatena kho dāni mayaṃ etarahi attanā viharāma akaraṇīyā asurehī’ti. "
msgstr "‘Now we’re in a secure location and the demons can’t do anything to us.’ "

msgctxt "an9.39:2.9"
msgid "Asurānampi, bhikkhave, etadahosi: "
msgstr "The demons also thought, "

msgctxt "an9.39:2.10"
msgid "‘bhīruttānagatena kho dāni devā etarahi attanā viharanti akaraṇīyā amhehī’ti. "
msgstr "‘Now the gods are in a secure location and we can’t do anything to them.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc3
msgctxt "an9.39:3.1"
msgid "Bhūtapubbaṃ, bhikkhave, devāsurasaṅgāmo samupabyūḷho ahosi. "
msgstr "Once upon a time, a battle was fought between the gods and the demons. "

msgctxt "an9.39:3.2"
msgid "Tasmiṃ kho pana, bhikkhave, saṅgāme devā jiniṃsu, asurā parājayiṃsu. "
msgstr "In that battle the gods won and the demons lost. "

msgctxt "an9.39:3.3"
msgid "Parājitā ca, bhikkhave, asurā apayiṃsuyeva dakkhiṇenābhimukhā, abhiyiṃsu devā. "
msgstr "Defeated, the demons fled south with the gods in pursuit. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an9.39:3.4"
msgid "Atha kho, bhikkhave, asurānaṃ etadahosi: "
msgstr "Then the demons thought, "

msgctxt "an9.39:3.5"
msgid "‘abhiyanteva kho devā. "
msgstr "‘The gods are still in pursuit. "

msgctxt "an9.39:3.6"
msgid "Yannūna mayaṃ dutiyampi devehi saṅgāmeyyāmā’ti. "
msgstr "Why don’t we engage them in battle a second time?’ "

msgctxt "an9.39:3.7"
msgid "Dutiyampi kho, bhikkhave, asurā devehi saṅgāmesuṃ. "
msgstr "And so a second battle was fought between the gods and the demons. "

msgctxt "an9.39:3.8"
msgid "Dutiyampi kho, bhikkhave, devā jiniṃsu, asurā parājayiṃsu. "
msgstr "And for a second time the gods won and the demons lost. "

msgctxt "an9.39:3.9"
msgid "Parājitā ca, bhikkhave, asurā apayiṃsuyeva dakkhiṇenābhimukhā, abhiyiṃsu devā. "
msgstr "Defeated, the demons fled south with the gods in pursuit. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc4
msgctxt "an9.39:4.1"
msgid "Atha kho, bhikkhave, asurānaṃ etadahosi: "
msgstr "Then the demons thought, "

msgctxt "an9.39:4.2"
msgid "‘abhiyanteva kho devā. "
msgstr "‘The gods are still in pursuit. "

msgctxt "an9.39:4.3"
msgid "Yannūna mayaṃ tatiyampi devehi saṅgāmeyyāmā’ti. "
msgstr "Why don’t we engage them in battle a third time?’ "

msgctxt "an9.39:4.4"
msgid "Tatiyampi kho, bhikkhave, asurā devehi saṅgāmesuṃ. "
msgstr "And so a third battle was fought between the gods and the demons. "

msgctxt "an9.39:4.5"
msgid "Tatiyampi kho, bhikkhave, devā jiniṃsu, asurā parājayiṃsu. "
msgstr "And for a third time the gods won and the demons lost. "

msgctxt "an9.39:4.6"
msgid "Parājitā ca, bhikkhave, asurā bhītā asurapuraṃyeva pavisiṃsu. "
msgstr "Defeated and terrified, the demons fled right into the citadel of the demons. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an9.39:4.7"
msgid "Asurapuragatānañca pana, bhikkhave, asurānaṃ etadahosi: "
msgstr "When they had entered their citadel, they thought, "

msgctxt "an9.39:4.8"
msgid "‘bhīruttānagatena kho dāni mayaṃ etarahi attanā viharāma akaraṇīyā devehī’ti. "
msgstr "‘Now we’re in a secure location and the gods can’t do anything to us.’ "

msgctxt "an9.39:4.9"
msgid "Devānampi, bhikkhave, etadahosi: "
msgstr "And the gods also thought, "

msgctxt "an9.39:4.10"
msgid "‘bhīruttānagatena kho dāni asurā etarahi attanā viharanti akaraṇīyā amhehī’ti. "
msgstr "‘Now the demons are in a secure location and we can’t do anything to them.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli4.434, sc5
msgctxt "an9.39:5.1"
msgid "Evamevaṃ kho, bhikkhave, yasmiṃ samaye bhikkhu vivicceva kāmehi vivicca akusalehi dhammehi savitakkaṃ savicāraṃ vivekajaṃ pītisukhaṃ paṭhamaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati, "
msgstr "In the same way, a mendicant, quite secluded from sensual pleasures, secluded from unskillful qualities, enters and remains in the first absorption, which has the rapture and bliss born of seclusion, while placing the mind and keeping it connected. "

msgctxt "an9.39:5.2"
msgid "tasmiṃ, bhikkhave, samaye bhikkhussa evaṃ hoti: "
msgstr "At such a time the mendicant thinks, "

msgctxt "an9.39:5.3"
msgid "‘bhīruttānagatena kho dānāhaṃ etarahi attanā viharāmi akaraṇīyo mārassā’ti. "
msgstr "‘Now I’m in a secure location and Māra can’t do anything to me.’ "

msgctxt "an9.39:5.4"
msgid "Mārassāpi, bhikkhave, pāpimato evaṃ hoti: "
msgstr "And Māra the Wicked also thinks, "

msgctxt "an9.39:5.5"
msgid "‘bhīruttānagatena kho dāni bhikkhu etarahi attanā viharati akaraṇīyo mayhan’ti. "
msgstr "‘Now the mendicant is in a secure location and we can’t do anything to them.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc6
msgctxt "an9.39:6.1"
msgid "Yasmiṃ, bhikkhave, samaye bhikkhu vitakkavicārānaṃ vūpasamā … pe … dutiyaṃ jhānaṃ … "
msgstr "When, as the placing of the mind and keeping it connected are stilled, a mendicant enters and remains in the second absorption … "

msgctxt "an9.39:6.2"
msgid "tatiyaṃ jhānaṃ … "
msgstr "third absorption … "

msgctxt "an9.39:6.3"
msgid "catutthaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati, "
msgstr "fourth absorption. "

msgctxt "an9.39:6.4"
msgid "tasmiṃ, bhikkhave, samaye bhikkhussa evaṃ hoti: "
msgstr "At such a time the mendicant thinks, "

msgctxt "an9.39:6.5"
msgid "‘bhīruttānagatena kho dānāhaṃ etarahi attanā viharāmi akaraṇīyo mārassā’ti. "
msgstr "‘Now I’m in a secure location and Māra can’t do anything to me.’ "

msgctxt "an9.39:6.6"
msgid "Mārassāpi, bhikkhave, pāpimato evaṃ hoti: "
msgstr "And Māra the Wicked also thinks, "

msgctxt "an9.39:6.7"
msgid "‘bhīruttānagatena kho dāni bhikkhu etarahi attanā viharati, akaraṇīyo mayhan’ti. "
msgstr "‘Now the mendicant is in a secure location and we can’t do anything to them.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc7
msgctxt "an9.39:7.1"
msgid "Yasmiṃ, bhikkhave, samaye bhikkhu sabbaso rūpasaññānaṃ samatikkamā paṭighasaññānaṃ atthaṅgamā nānattasaññānaṃ amanasikārā ‘ananto ākāso’ti ākāsānañcāyatanaṃ upasampajja viharati. "
msgstr "A mendicant, going totally beyond perceptions of form, with the ending of perceptions of impingement, not focusing on perceptions of diversity, aware that ‘space is infinite’, enters and remains in the dimension of infinite space. "

# NOTE: See BB for textual difficulties with this passage. To these we can add the inclusion in MS of tinno loke visattikam, which is clearly a mistake and should apply only to the final item. Finally the arupa sections are missing tasmim samaye.
msgctxt "an9.39:7.2"
msgid "Ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, ‘bhikkhu antamakāsi māraṃ, apadaṃ vadhitvā māracakkhuṃ adassanaṃ gato pāpimato tiṇṇo loke visattikan’ti. "
msgstr "At such a time they are called a mendicant who has blinded Māra, put out his eyes without a trace, and gone where the Wicked One cannot see. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc8
msgctxt "an9.39:8.1"
msgid "Yasmiṃ, bhikkhave, samaye bhikkhu sabbaso ākāsānañcāyatanaṃ samatikkamma ‘anantaṃ viññāṇan’ti viññāṇañcāyatanaṃ upasampajja viharati … "
msgstr "A mendicant, going totally beyond the dimension of infinite space, aware that ‘consciousness is infinite’, enters and remains in the dimension of infinite consciousness. … "

msgctxt "an9.39:8.2"
msgid "sabbaso viññāṇañcāyatanaṃ samatikkamma ‘natthi kiñcī’ti ākiñcaññāyatanaṃ upasampajja viharati … "
msgstr "Going totally beyond the dimension of infinite consciousness, aware that ‘there is nothing at all’, they enter and remain in the dimension of nothingness. … "

msgctxt "an9.39:8.3"
msgid "sabbaso ākiñcaññāyatanaṃ samatikkamma nevasaññānāsaññāyatanaṃ upasampajja viharati … "
msgstr "Going totally beyond the dimension of nothingness, they enter and remain in the dimension of neither perception nor non-perception. … "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an9.39:8.4"
msgid "sabbaso nevasaññānāsaññāyatanaṃ samatikkamma saññāvedayitanirodhaṃ upasampajja viharati, paññāya cassa disvā āsavā parikkhīṇā honti. "
msgstr "Going totally beyond the dimension of neither perception nor non-perception, they entersand remain in the cessation of perception and feeling. And, having seen with wisdom, their defilements come to an end. "

msgctxt "an9.39:8.5"
msgid "Ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, ‘bhikkhu antamakāsi māraṃ, apadaṃ vadhitvā māracakkhuṃ adassanaṃ gato pāpimato tiṇṇo loke visattikan’”ti. "
msgstr "At such a time they are called a mendicant who has blinded Māra, put out his eyes without a trace, and gone where the Wicked One cannot see. And they’ve crossed over clinging to the world.” "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an9.39:8.6"
msgid "Aṭṭhamaṃ. "
msgstr ""

